This page lists all the noiselog years that are present on this site.
Note how the top navigation menu doesn't link to this page, but instead links
to the latest noiselog year directly.

The reason for adopting this structure is to make sure that links that exist in
the wild to entries to our noiselog don't become invalidated when a new year comes
around and we rotate the noiselog feed.

Noiselog rotation ensures that you don't have a single page that grows
indefinitely, eventually compromising your editing expreience and worsening your
user's browsing experience. You can use any arbitrary policy (even deleting old
entries if you are fine with having a more ephemeral noiselog), but cutting them
by year is a good default option. 

When rotating a noiselog all you have to do is create a new page with a newer
date set in the frontmatter `date` field, and update the page description to let
people know that this page is not the current year's noiselog anymore.

The latest noiselog year is also available [via RSS feed]($link.alternative('rss')).
